String Methods– Slicing for sub strings

    • Obtaining a portion of a string (sub String) is called slicing.
    • myName[0:6] will return the sub-string starting from 0th position UP TO (but not inclusive) 6th position.

Summary of String Methods

Method

Description

len()

Eg. len(myString)

Returns the length of the string myString

myString.upper()

Returns the upper case value of myString

myString.lower()

Returns the lower case value of myString

myString.split()

Returns a list of sub-strings after splitting the string using the white space character. Can split using a given separator eg. myString.split(‘-’).

myString.isdigit()

Returns TRUE if a given character is a digit.

myString.isalpha()

Returns TRUE if a given character is an alphabetic character.

 myString.startswith()

Returns TRUE if a String starts up with a given sub string.

Eg. myString.startswith(sub_string)

 myString.endswith()

Returns TRUE if a String ends up with a given sub string

 Join()

Joins the letters/items in a list (letters =[‘ab’, ‘ba’]) with a given character. Eg. myString = ‘-‘ .join(letters)

myString = ab-ba

 myString.find()

Finds the first occurrence of a sub string and returns it position

myString.strip()

Removes all leading or trailing white spaces around myString

Class Exercise 2

  1. Find the length of myString using a command.
  2. Write a command to display the first letter (‘T’) of myString.
  3. Write a command to display the last letter (the ! mark) of myString.
  4. Give a command to display the first 5 charactors of myString.
  5. Display myString 4 times.
  6. Write a command to display sub-string ‘on the mat!’ (Hint: use find() method)
  7. Write commands to display a list with elements ['The', 'cat', 'sat', 'on', 'the', 'mat!']
  8. Print the entire string in lower case.
  9. Print the sub string ‘on the mat!’ in upper case.
  10. Check if the entire string is alphabetic characters.
  11. Check if the string ends with the character ‘!’.
  12. Join the letters: ‘a’, ‘w’, ‘s’, ‘o’, ‘m’, ‘e’ in the given order, to form a word
  13. Return the index position of ‘sat’ in myString.
  14. Remove the exclamation mark from myString.

26

File operations

Method

Description

open(filename, mode)

Opens a file at a given pathname and returns a file object. Mode can be ‘r’, ‘w’, ‘rw’, or ‘a’

‘r’ – read

‘w’ – write

‘rw’ – read and write

‘a’ - append

f.close()

Closes a file after writing. No need to close a file after reading.

f.write(stringvalue)

Writes a string value.

f.read()

Reads and returns entire content of a file as a single string value. If end of file reached returns ‘ ‘.

f.readline()

Reads file contents line by line. If end of file reached returns ‘ ‘.
